<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900409-0026</DOCNO><DOCID>900409-0026.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Ford Motor Co.:   International Plans Could   Result From Fiat Discussion</HL><DATE>04/09/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A5</SO><CO>   F FIA</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)FARM EQUIPMENT (FAR)</IN><LP>   Ford Motor Co. and the Fiat Group of Italy confirmed theyare holding talks that could lead to world-wide arrangementsinvolving their tractor and farm equipment operations, whilepreserving their product and market identities.   The two companies also said they are exploring, inseparate discussions, possible areas of cooperation in theheavy-truck business. Both companies said they have agreedthat no further announcement will be made until there aredefinitive agreements.</LP><TEXT>   Friday's announcement followed reports that Dearborn,Mich.-based Ford and Fiat are discussing the possible sale ofFord's New Holland farm-equipment subsidiary to Fiat. Such asale would be consistent with Ford's recent strategy ofshedding non-automotive operations; for example, the automaker has put its aerospace unit up for sale.   Ford and Fiat are partners in the heavy-truck business inEurope.</TEXT></DOC>